<br>
Honestly, I would much rather kill something on the first shot and shrug off wasted plat than try to preserve money and waste time on CR. =p<br>
<br>
I mildly disagree about AC/HP/resists. I think it's situational. If you have say a tank dragon with weak spells, I go all AC/HP and leave my entire resist kit bagged. I have found that merely being level 60 with decent resists on normal gear is sufficient for these encounters. If you have a strong caster dragon I totally ignore AC and go all HP/resists. I look like a newb in the screenshots, but I am usually alive to see the wurm fall. =p<br>
