  Just a few more suggestions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ulindaariceblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lindaar Iceblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(9/20/01 8:42:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How to stay alive in dragon encounters.</span><hr size=1> I firmly believe in AC, unless I'm fighting a strong caster mob with weak melee ability. The way I see it, even if your AC saves you one hit, that's normally going to be a 700+ hit. The HPs you save from having a 700+ hit miss is a ton more than you'll ever get from +HP by switching out AC.<br>
<br>
